cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the classification of speech utterances into system-directed and non-system-directed categories using neural network architectures. This falls under the sub-category of Speech and Dialogue Processing (cs.SD) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The use of attention mechanisms is a popular technique in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML), which makes cs.LG and cs.AI also likely sub-categories.
